            <p>Dr. Norman Borlaug (1914-2009) was an American agronomist who led initiatives worldwide that contributed to extensive increases in agricultural production termed the Green Revolution. For his extraordinary achievements, Dr. Borlaug received the Nobel Peace Prize in 1970.</p>
